Baker Technology, Singapore Post, SMRT: Singapore Stocks Preview

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 
2011-05-02T05:10:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/baker-technology-singapore-post-smrt-singapore-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  Singapore  trading tomorrow. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and share prices are from the
previous close.  Singapore’s Straits Times Index fell 0.2 percent to
3,179.86 on April 29. The market was closed yesterday for a
public holiday.  Baker Technology Ltd. (BTL)  : The supplier of equipment
to the oil and gas industry said first-quarter revenue increased
71 percent to S$10.6 million ($8.7 million). Baker Technology
dropped 2.4 percent to 41.5 Singapore cents.  Noble Group Ltd. (NOBL)  : The Hong Kong-based supplier of
commodities increased and Korea Investment Corp. have entered
into a strategic agreement to invest in infrastructure assets,
Noble said in a statement to the Singapore stock exchange. Noble
rose 1.4 percent to S$2.23.  Singapore Post Ltd. (SPOST)  : The operator of the city’s
post offices said fourth-quarter net income declined 9.6 percent
from a year earlier to S$37 million. The company said it is
cautiously optimistic on its outlook and is looking for
acquisitions in Singapore and in  Asia . The stock gained 0.9
percent to S$1.16.  SMRT Corp. (MRT SP): Singapore’s biggest commuter-train
operator said fourth-quarter net income increased 50 percent to
S$34 million from a year earlier. SMRT was unchanged at S$1.90.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Burgos in Singapore at 
